 President Muhammadu Buhari is currently presiding over the second virtual Federal Executive Council FEC meeting in Abuja. The President, it was gathered, has a few of the members of the council in attendance, while most of the others are connecting via videoconferencing. Today’s FEC meeting is the second virtual FEC meeting since the coronavirus pandemic started. The first was held last week Wednesday. The virtual option was adopted as part of measures to guard against the spread of the virus. Only ministers with memos to present are the ones who need to be physically present at the State House for the meeting.  Details shortly…